fields.descriptive_line: Children's bedroom room setting including a wardrobe, a shelf, a fireplace, kite, and other accessories, part of a dolls' house in the style of the 1940s made in England by Roma Hopkinson in the late 1980s to late 1990s
fields.physical_description:
[room setting] Children's bedroom with parquet effect flooring, yellow wallpaper with a blue floral print, two working light fittings, a fireplace and mantelpiece with a clock, horse statue and a fox statue attached. There is a shelf running around two sides of the room with dolls, a Golliwog, a clock and a glass jar on top. On the wall are three framed photographs, a mirror, a kite, and a painting of a badger. In the right-hand corner of the room is a brown wooden wardrobe attached to the wall containing clothes.
[beds (furniture)] Wooden single bed with headboard, painted white. The bed has a mattress covered with a pink fabric printed with pink and green flowers. There are two cream pillows, two sheets, three blankets, and a floral quilt.
[beds (furniture)] Wooden single bed with headboard, painted brown. The bed has a mattress covered with blue and white gingham fabric. There are two cream pillows, two sheets, three blankets, and a floral quilt.
[chests] Long wooden chest, stained dark brown. The lid of the chest is hinged allowing it to be opened up with a storage space underneath.
[chairs] Wardrobe unit with one tall cupboard, a swivelling long mirror with a drawer beneath. Fixed to the top of the cupboard is a lamp, dollhouse, and toy ball. In front of the mirror is a pair of miniature gold scissors, a conker attached to a piece of string, a hairbrush, comb, and hand held mirror. Inside the wardrobe are five clothes hangers and a pair of red wellington boots.
[tables (support furniture)] Wooden chest with four drawers and a smaller drawer on top beneath a shelf. Fixed to the top of the chest is an oval photograph frame, a model squirrel, a model bear, and a woman figurine.
[rugs] Wooden chest with four drawers stained brown with round, gold painted handles. Fixed to the top of the chest is a blue dolls' house, books, bookends, a green model elephant, a skipping rope and a tadpole in a jar.
[dolls' house accessories] Brown wooden chair with carved back and silver polyester covered seat cushion.
[dolls' house toys] Wooden bedside table with two shelves stained brown.
[chests of drawers] Two patterned rugs with cream fringing at each end.
[chests of drawers] Assortment of dolls' house accessories including a paper shopping bag with gifts, two wooden animal statues, a model cat, a straw bonnet, a hot water bottle, a wooden box with miniature safety pins inside, a gold key, a pink jewel, three torches, and a banana and apple core on a plate.
[wardrobes (case furniture)] An assortment of miniature toys for a dolls' house including a tea set, a tennis racket, a game of Chinese Chequers, a pair of roller skates, two toy badgers, a doll made from plastic beads, two clown models, two Golliwog toys, a colouring book with crayons, a box of pencils, two dolls sitting on alphabet blocks, Russian dolls, a paint set, a ball game, and a zylophone. Also, there are five painted metal toys with moving limbs including a Golliwog, Humpty Dumpty, a teddy bear, a white rabbit, a bear dressed as Santa Claus and the Owl and the Pussycat in a pea-green boat with a guitar, jar of honey and money.

fields.public_access_description: This house is a replica of a real house in Surrey where Roma Hopkinson lived with her family during the Second World War. Roma built this house in the 1980's, paying incredible attention to detail, reproducing ration books, identity cards, newspapers, and photo albums by reducing copies of the original versions. The photographs show her family as they appeared at that time. Each doll is also modelled on a family member with Roma appearing as one on of the children in a school dress. The house accurately reflects the wartime era, showing popular products, foodstuffs, games, and furnishings from the time.
